docs.lead_paragraph: FORTY-EIGHT hours after the first Allied troops had scrambled ashore in Sicily a brisk, bulky figure wearing a spotless summer uniform with the four stars that denote the rank of a full general in the Army of the United States climbed onto the deck of an Army transport, walked quickly to the rail and gazed searchingly at the gray mass of Sicily on the horizon.
